What's this?
---

Helper scripts to plot buffer status graph of VisualizerCapturedAudioDataBuffer class.


Requirements
---

- Android Studio or Eclipse (ADT)
- ADB
- Python
- Gnuplot


Usage
---
1. Uncomment the LOG_TAG definition line in VisualizerCapturedAudioDataBuffer.cpp (or HQVisualizerCapturedAudioDataBuffer.cpp)
2. Rebuild and install the OpenSLMediaPlayerExample app
3. Open this directory with terminal app
4. Run ./capture_buffer_log.sh to start logging
5. Stop logging by Ctrl+C
6. Run ./split_log.sh
7. Run gnuplot and input the following command 
  load "plot.plt"
